summary:
You have a train to catch!
For Acen this year I wanted to try something else nobody else has: Spiderman stopping the train from...
body:
You have a train to catch!

For Acen this year I wanted to try something else nobody else has: Spiderman stopping the train from Spider-Man 2. I already had the suit, so I figured I’d paint a train car and go with it.

The response to this was overwhelming, and I was not at all expecting this to be as popular as it was.

title: Dating Peter Parker would include:
body:
• Dating Peter means having cute nicknames for each other that make all the adults in the room cringe
  • Although normally he just calls you “Baby” or “Babe”
  • Peter needs someone he can geek out with, either about comic books or old computers.
  • Even if you’re not into it yourself, he still wants to share his interests with you. In return he’ll take an interest in whatever you like a well
  • If you’re struggling with any of your school subjects, Peter jumps at the opportunity to tutor you, even just so the two of you can spend some time together
  • He probably invites you round for study dates and the two of you sit in his room listening to music and doing homework
  • Aunt May would keep interrupting and coming into his room with various excuses like laundry or offering snacks. Sometimes she doesn’t even make one and just barges in
  • She actually really likes you and is always asking Peter about you when you’re not there
  • “So when’s that pretty girl/boy, Y/N coming back? You and them seem quite close…”
  • Queue blushing
  • Peter actually blushes quite a lot, especially if you kiss him in public. He’ll always kiss you back but that doesn’t stop the red on his cheeks
  • Normally he’ll just give you a peck on the cheek, intense public make out sessions aren’t really his style
  • Peter likes to have an arm around your shoulders or your waist, your presence comforting him and helping him to focus
  • He needs someone who can support him with all the avengers business and with his powers. It’s a lot of responsibility so he needs someone that will listen to him
  • Having yu around no doubt makes it a lot easier on him, and he can’t help but constantly bring you up to his friends
  • This has probably prompted Tony to meet you, turning up at your house unexpectedly and interrogating you about your intentions with his adopted son
  • Of course, he’ll realise how nice you are and how much Peter means to you and from then on your relationship has the Tony Stark seal of approval
